**Section 80D** provides a deduction for health insurance premiums paid for yourself, your spouse, dependent children, and parents. The deduction is ₹25,000 for self + family (₹50,000 if you are a senior citizen) and up to ₹25,000 additional for parents (₹50,000 if parents are senior citizens), giving a maximum of ₹75,000 per year.
